This paper is about evaluating the natural gradient algorithm for learning deep models, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of unlabeled data to improve generalization error, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper explores the incorporation of second-order information, which is a topic in optimization (cs.OH) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.NE, followed by cs.CV, cs.CL, and cs.AI.
